Package com.google.code.rees.scope.util.monitor

Class com.google.code.rees.scope.util.monitor.BasicTimeoutMonitor extends Object implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: -7924540987291582366L

Serialization Methods

readObject

private void readObject(ObjectInputStream ois)
                 throws ClassNotFoundException,
                        IOException
An override of the readObject method for serialization. It calls BasicTimeoutMonitor.init() after deserialization in order to startup a new BasicTimeoutMonitor.taskThread and assign it the BasicTimeoutMonitor.timeoutTasks in order to have the monitor continue monitoring after serialization.

Throws:
ClassNotFoundException
IOException

writeObject

private void writeObject(ObjectOutputStream oos)
                  throws IOException
An override of the writeObject method for serialization. It just makes sure that the BasicTimeoutMonitor.taskThread is destroyed. Not likely to be necessary in the real world, but good for a safe measure.

Throws:
IOException
